node.name: CRISPRGenie
node.description: A GPT model to generate sgRNA sequences based on provided gene IDs. By incorporating a custom tokenizer and beam search, the model produces high-probability sgRNA sequences, facilitating efficient and targeted gene editing applications.

node.name: MolGraphNet
node.description: A machine learning project using directed message passing neural networks (D-MPNN) to predict molecular properties from SMILES strings, inspired by the Chemprop model.

node.name: Bioactivity_Prediction_App
node.description: A web application for predicting the bioactivity of small molecules using machine learning models
